\begin_layout Subsection

\lang english
Bogle Variant Rule
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Bogle variant method would have Jennifer invest 100 minus her age in
 stocks and the remainder of her savings in bonds and cash (as well as the
 overlay).
 This rule is a simplistic way to have Jennifer invest in a more conservative
 way as she approaches retirement.
 We feel that this rule is overly simplistic and we see this in the performance
 of the strategy.
 
\end_layout

