\begin_layout Subsection

\lang english
Funding Ratio Rule
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This method takes into account Jennifer's funding ratio and uses it as a
 metric to assess her asset allocation.
 As Jennifer's funding ratio approaches one, we assume that she will want
 to invest more conservatively to be more certain that she will reach her
 goals.
 With this rule, Jennifer will be more certain that she will be able to
 fund her retirement by a given age, but she will be less likely to have
 the opportunity to retire early.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection

\lang english
Fixed Juncture Rule
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This rule incorporates the fixed mix policy rule with something like the
 Bogle variant rule.
 Instead of changing the percentages in each asset annually, we instead
 change the percentages every ten years so that Jennifer can keep a higher
 percentage of her assets in stocks for longer.
 This methodology would hopefully lead to Jennifer having a higher probability
 of retiring at an earlier age.
 
\end_layout

